  "id": "BIT-discourse-2025-61598",
  "summary": "Discourse is missing Cache-Control response header on error responses",
  "details": "Discourse is an open source discussion platform. Version before 3.6.2 and 3.6.0.beta2, default Cache-Control response header with value no-store, no-cache was missing from error responses. This may caused unintended caching of those responses by proxies potentially leading to cache poisoning attacks. This vulnerability is fixed in 3.6.2 and 3.6.0.beta2.",
